{"name": "ci-test-toolkit", "metadata": {"name": "ci-test-toolkit", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL 2.0)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A framework for static analysis testing of CI configurations.", "upload_time": 1732235924}, "documentation": ["# CI Test\n## Evan Kohilas\n\nA framework for static analysis testing of CI configurations.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall using `pipx install ci-test-toolkit` to add `ci-test` to your PATH.\n\nThe tool can be run either via `ci-test` once installed or `python -m ci_test` from within the `src` folder.\n\n## Example\n\n`ci-test gitlab rule-snapshot <path_to_json>` will create a snapshot of your ci configuration, by listing all rulesets and the jobs that will run for each of them.\n\nThis snapshot can then be used to generate diffs of the linking between jobs and their rules.\n\n## Input Generation\n\nCurrently the tool is setup to take input of the following form:\n\n```json\n[\n    {\n        \"name\": \"job-name\",\n        \"rules\": [\n            {\n                \"if\": \"$CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == 'push'\"\n            },\n            {\n                \"if\": \"$CI_PIPELINE_SOURCE == 'merge_request_event'\",\n                \"changes\": [\n                    \"**/*.py\"\n                ]\n            },\n        ]\n    }\n]\n```\n\nThis is easiest made using [gitlab-ci-local](https://github.com/firecow/gitlab-ci-local)\n\nWith `node` installed, run `npx gitlab-ci-local --list-json > gitlab-ci-local.json` in a project directory with a `.gitlab-ci.yml` file.\n\nThen, run `ci-test gitlab rule-snapshot gitlab-ci-local.json` to create a collated snapshot.\n\n## TODO\n\n- Remove the dependency on `gitlab-ci-local`\n- Support GitHub configurations\n- Add more testing commands\n- Add better CLI\n- Add linting/formatting\n- Clean up for best practices\n\n## Contibuting\n\nPlease see `CONTRIBUTING.md` for a head start.\n\nPull requests welcome!\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ci_test", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ci_test.main", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ci_test.main.main", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "json_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ci_test.cli", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ci_test.cli.cli", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ci_test.__main__", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ci_test.job_rules", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ci_test.job_rules.IfRule", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ci_test.job_rules.IfRule.condition", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "ci_test.job_rules.GlobPath", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ci_test.job_rules.GlobPath.glob_path", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "ci_test.job_rules.ChangesRule", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ci_test.job_rules.ChangesRule.changes", "type": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "GlobPath", "xref": {"fqname": "ci_test.job_rules.GlobPath", "project": n